main event: Witnesses reported seeing three disc-shaped objects over Texas on May 8, 1959.
interesting points: The objects were estimated to be 40 to 60 feet in diameter and moving at an estimated speed of 800 mph.
The objects were observed for approximately 5 minutes before disappearing to the northeast.
Two independent observers provided consistent reports of the sighting.
The location of the sighting was approximately 12 miles east of Austin, Texas.
The sighting was investigated by the United States Air Force as part of Project Blue Book.
